<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Glad we stayed at the Eliot After reading many reviews on this site, I finally decided on the Eliot for our March 2004 Looking for Colleges trip. We couldn't have been happier. They state on their website that they will match all internet offerings and sure enough I did find a lower rate which they immediately booked for us. When we arrived they were out of the standard rooms so we were upgraded to a very nice top floor suite. We asked for a recommendation for dinner on Newbury Street for Saturday night and they quickly got us a reservation at a great Italian Restaurant (Papa Razzi). Breakfast scones were wonderful and the coffee was good and strong. All in all it was just the kind of small boutique hotel experience I was looking for. 
