<Content>Great and Comfortable We had two nights at this hotel in March, 2004. This is a boutique hotel with large comfortable rooms. The desk staff was helpful and nice. The doorman and bellhops were very helpful and pleasant and enhanced our stay.This hotel is in a wonderful location, a block from a T stop, only a hop and skip to Cambridge, in a lovely neighborhood. It is the former home of a president of Harvard, lovely entrance. It was like staying in a gracious host's guest rooms.The only negative is that we had two adjoining rooms on the 4th floor facing on Massacusetts Avenue which can be noisy late into the night. We were so tired the second night, we got used to it, but light sleepers beware.I would not hesitate to return to this hotel. 
